question: Can I go 2 weeks after the election without finding out who won?

content.text: I really think i can do it.
I will stop listening to podcasts and following polls 5 weeks (

) before the election. I will pause my twitter. I will tell my coworkers and family not to tell me and avoid looking at newspapers. I will not watch any TV. I will not turn on the radio.  I will camp for the night of the election outside of the very blue city where I live so I don’t hear celebrations. I will work from home for 3-4 business days after the election. I will not look at YouTube or tiktok.
Not betting in this market so I am not biased.
